      "words": [
        "As",
        "a",
        "child"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "Claudia spent hours on end with her pony.",
      "start": 189.42,
      "end": 191.9,
      "words": [
        "Claudia",
        "spent",
        "hours",
        "on",
        "end",
        "with",
        "her",
        "pony"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "Phrases like 'days or hours on end' mean days or hours doing something continuously without stopping.",
      "start": 192.3,
      "end": 198.46,
      "words": [
        "Phrases",
        "like",
        "'days",
        "or",
        "hours",
        "on",
        "end'",
        "mean",
        "days",
        "or",
        "hours",
        "doing",
        "something",
        "continuously",
        "without",
        "stopping"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "Spending time with her pony helped Claudia through puberty,",
      "start": 198.54,
      "end": 201.58,
      "words": [
        "Spending",
        "time",
        "with",
        "her",
        "pony",
        "helped",
        "Claudia",
        "through",
        "puberty"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "the stage of life when a child grows into an adult because of changes in their body which allow them to have children.",
      "start": 201.74,
      "end": 207.66,
      "words": [
        "the",
        "stage",
        "of",
        "life",
        "when",
        "a",
        "child",
        "grows",
        "into",
        "an",
        "adult",
        "because",
        "of",
        "changes",
        "in",
        "their",
        "body",
        "which",
        "allow",
        "them",
        "to",
        "have",
        "children"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "It was her teenage experiences that led Claudia to start her own horse therapy centre.",
      "start": 207.98,
      "end": 212.7,
      "words": [
        "It",
        "was",
        "her",
        "teenage",
        "experiences",
        "that",
        "led",
        "Claudia",
        "to",
        "start",
        "her",
        "own",
        "horse",
        "therapy",
        "centre"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "She works a lot with teenage girls and children in care.",
      "start": 212.94,
      "end": 215.9,
      "words": [
        "She",
        "works",
        "a",
        "lot",
        "with",
        "teenage",
        "girls",
        "and",
        "children",
        "in",
        "care"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "A child in care is a child who's being looked after by the local authorities because they cannot be cared for by their parents or family.",
      "start": 216.3,
      "end": 223.82,
      "words": [
        "A",
        "child",
        "in",
        "care",
        "is",
        "a",
        "child",
        "who's",
        "being",
        "looked",
        "after",
        "by",
        "the",
        "local",
        "authorities",
        "because",
        "they",
        "cannot",
        "be",
        "cared",
        "for",
        "by",
        "their",
        "parents",
        "or",
        "family"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "Here,",
      "start": 224.62,
      "end": 224.94,
      "words": [
        "Here"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "Claudia talks more about her work with children and horses to BBC World Service's The Conversation.",
      "start": 224.94,
      "end": 230.7,
      "words": [
        "Claudia",
        "talks",
        "more",
        "about",
        "her",
        "work",
        "with",
        "children",
        "and",
        "horses",
        "to",
        "BBC",
        "World",
        "Service's",
        "The",
        "Conversation"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "It would take maybe a few sessions for a relationship of trust to be formed,",
      "start": 231.292,
      "end": 237.372,
      "words": [
        "It",
        "would",
        "take",
        "maybe",
        "a",
        "few",
        "sessions",
        "for",
        "a",
        "relationship",
        "of",
        "trust",
        "to",
        "be",
        "formed"
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "and it's quite extraordinary to see a child that's experienced a lot of trauma,",
      "start": 238.172,
      "end": 244.092,
      "words": [
        "and",
        "it's",
        "quite",
        "extraordinary",
        "to",
        "see",
        "a",
        "child",
        "that's",
        "experienced",
        "a",
        "lot",
        "of",
        "trauma"
